post_text: In light of the racial injustices going on today, we strive for peace and equity within our schools. We hope and pray that we can encourage our students to love each other, because we know together we can make a difference. We will continue our passionate pursuit of excellent education for all children and use that as a means to change the dynamics of a broken system. There is no place for racism, hatred, or social injustice in our schools and in our world. We ask that you join us in the commitment to keeping these promises to our students and families.

8th Grade Spotlight: Riley Martinez
Riley was apprehensive when she found out her family was moving here from TX, but she was grateful to be able to attend ARCA for her 8th grade year. She is appreciative of her teachers and has made some great friends. Riley has been through a lot in her life so far, but she always keeps her head up and a smile on her face. Her family is very important to her, especially her Nana who taught her how to cook and bake. Riley’s favorite quote is: Shoot for the moon. Even if you miss, you’ll land among the stars.” -Norman Vincent Peale

8th grade spotlight:

Claire Urdaz is an 8th grade Cambridge student at ARCA. She has been at ARCA since the day it opened its doors. Her favorite subject is ELA because it helps her to be a creative thinker and writer, which are skills that she can use in every subject. At ARCA, she have been a cheerleader and has participated in volleyball, basketball, and track. Claire is also the Beta Club Secretary. She plans to become an engineer after graduation. ARCA was lucky to have a student like Claire!

We are excited to see where the next 4 years will bring her.

post_text:
Thanks to everyone who participated in the #ARCA5K. The event was a huge success! We had over 200 submissions and our school community covered 478.6 miles during the week! That's enough running to reach cities like San Antonio, Atlanta, and Nashville!

5. 5th Grade - 28.8 miles
4. 1st Grade - 31 miles
3. 8th Grade - 54.6 miles
2. 4th grade - 56.4 miles
FACULTY/STAFF - 156.8 MILES
Thanks again to ALL of our participants! Hope everyone enjoyed the extra sweat! Geaux Eagles!

8th Grade Spotlight: Makalah Billiot

Makalah started ARCA this year and adjusted very well to life on campus. She loves her family and exploring new places. She works hard and is proud to say she stays on the Honor Roll. Music is a big part of her life. She plays the guitar and even some piano. Her future plans include becoming a music producer. She is already looking at all her options for college and hopes to end up in New York or California. The sky is the limit for Makalah!

post_text:
8th Grade Spotlight: Rylin Gaspard
Rylin’s favorite quote is one by Albert Einstein, “Never give up on what you really want to do. The person with big dreams is more powerful than the one with all the fears.” Rylin works hard to do her best in school each day. She also loves playing softball and has been on ARCA’s team for 3 years. She feels her grit and determination will help her make the high school softball team. In her spare time she loves four wheeling, fishing, hunting, and listening to country music. She plans to attend LSU or UL and work in the medical field. We know she is going places! Go get em’ Rylin!

8th Grade Spotlight: Laken Day

Laken has been at ARCA since the opening and decided to stay and continue her education at ARCA High. She really enjoys sports. She has been playing volleyball and basketball at ARCA for 4 years and plans to continue on playing through high school. While playing volleyball and basketball, she found a love for running and joined the track and cross country team. She would love to attend Brigham Young University, D1 school in Utah, on an academic or basketball scholarship or to UL, while majoring in either a pediatric surgeon or a physical therapist.

ARCA is proud to announce our Students of the Year! Our 5th grade Student of the Year is Ethan Roque, and our 8th grade Student of the Year is Charlotte Hawkins. Ethan and Charlotte won at both the school and regional level and will now compete again in February. We wish them the best of luck and know they will both represent the school well! Go Eagles!

Ethan is a proud fifth grader at ARCA. He has earned many academic honors and believes in hard work, determination, and always putting his best foot forward. Out of school, he spends his time practicing and playing basketball, football, and baseball. One day he hopes to become a professional athlete that can inspire our youth and give back to the community.

Charlotte has great plans for her future. She hopes to become a marine biologist or a business owner when she graduates from LSU. She currently enjoys playing volleyball and loves the positive environment here at ARCA. Her favorite quote is, " You will never regret being kind." -Unknown

post_text:
Staff Member of the Month
Mrs. Missy, Nurse
By Camryn B, Dillon D, and Olivia G (7th grade)

Mrs. Missy is a superhero nurse at Acadiana Renaissance. She has been a nurse for almost 5 years. She loves working here because the students are great and the teamwork between the co-workers and parents are amazing. Super Missy has a passion for helping others and found out about the job through one of her good friends coach Eaton. Most of the time kids come to her because of headaches and upset stomachs. She is a master of detecting when students are faking an injury.

She was born and raised as an LSU Tiger, but she also attended SLCC for her last years of college. Her first job was working in surgery for a surgeon. If she was a teacher she would teach math because it’s her favorite subject. Her favorite memory as a child was family gatherings, especially in the fall, and if she could time travel she would go back to the 70’s because she loved their music. The perfect vacation would be two days in Disney, two days at the beach, and two days skiing.

post_text:
Staff Member of the Month
Ms. Deidre, Custodian
By Laila J, Chris S, and Sophie L (6th Grade)

Ms. Deidre is a custodian at Acadiana Renaissance. She has been working here for five years. One of the reasons she loves her job is because she loves cleaning. Her first job was a pharmacy tech. When she was a little girl, she always wanted to be a mother. “After my kids were all in school, I was ready to reenter the work place. I found an opening at ARCA with hours that would be beneficial to still be a mother. That’s when I found my true passion of working with a wonderful staff and amazing students.”

Ms. Deidre loves Louisiana and is very passionate about Mardi Gras. It is her absolute favorite time of the year. Her other hobbies include spending time with family, shopping, and traveling. One of her dream vacation destinations is France. She is a big Dr. Pepper fan. She has two children and they are the loves of her life.

post_text:
Acadiana Renaissance Upper- Ground Breaking

On January 10th, 2020, the city of Youngsville, Louisiana came together for the groundbreaking ceremony of Acadiana Renaissance Charter Academy’s Upper School. In the first phase of the school opening in August of 2020, the building will serve grades 6-9. In phase two, the following school year, the campus will expand to a full 6-12 high school. The ceremony was attended by the Mayor of Youngsville, members of the city council, Louisiana state representatives, Lafayette Charter Foundation members, and the proud students and staff of ARCA.

Mayor, Ken Ritter said, “Education can unlock the world.” As a testimony to this, five years ago, the city councilman and Mayor of Youngsville took their oaths of office inside the school cafeteria of ARCA as a symbol of their commitment to education. He went on to thank CSUSA for their investment and partnership in the educational future of the community of Youngsville.

post_text:
October Staff Member of the Month

Ms. Manuel was originally going to be a mortician, but today she is a 4th and 5th grade interventionist at Acadiana Renaissance. She loves being in her current job because she enjoys helping kids grow and working with all the staff. Her favorite thing to teach is grammar and reading.

Ms. Manuel has two children and a dog. Decorating is one of her favorite hobbies, and she especially loves decorating houses. In her free time, she loves to garden. Her favorite memory as a child growing up was living in Hawaii and traveling to California to visit her father. David Gray is her favorite artist. Her favorite sport is baseball. Did you know her first job was at Hardee’s restaurant, which only lasted two days? Surprisingly one thing that has been a secret about her is that she is a homebody, because if you know her, she is funny and talkative.

post_text:
Mr. Bowe, August 2019 Staff Member of the Month

As the tallest person at Acadiana Renaissance, Mr. Bowe stands at a jaw-dropping 6 foot 6! He is the head of our I.T. department.

Curious about the iPhone as a teenager, he was inspired to work with technology. He never thought he would be working at a school, but is enjoying it so far. Recently most of his time has been occupied with re-imaging computers and helping the staff. On average he works with about 25 computers a day. His most rewarding part of the job is making sure the students have working technology.

Besides working with technology, he would’ve liked to teach P.E. In fact, one of his hobbies is playing basketball. Did you see him dunk at the staff versus student game? He also enjoys oldies and rap music. Apple or Android? “Apple, of course.” Chick-Fil-A, Canes, or Popeyes? All three because “they’re all super delicious.” Oh, and his favorite color wire is blue.

(Gaby, Sarah, and Olivia, 7th grade photography students)

Kindergarten testing for the 2019-2020 school year will be August 14th-16th. Parents of incoming KG students will receive a call to set up their child's testing time.

On Monday, August 19th, KG boys will report to school. Parents should park in the front parking lot and walk their child through the front office, between 8:30 and 9:00 am. On Tuesday, August 20th, KG boys will NOT report to school.

On Tuesday, August 20th, KG girls will report to school. Parents should park in the front parking lot and walk their child through the front office, between 8:30 and 9:00 am.

Meet & Greet will take place on Monday, August 19th for KG boys and Tuesday, August 20th for KG girls.

On Wednesday, August 21st, ALL KG students will report to school from 7:30-7:55 am. Parents will utilize the car lanes to drop-off their child. Student helpers will be on hand to walk KG students to their classrooms.

post_text: "Have you ever been somewhere that has a very welcoming atmosphere? Somewhere you could walk around the hallways and not feel pressured to be someone you aren't. I am very blessed that I have a place like this. This place is Acadiana Renaissance Charter Academy."

THU, FEB 7, 2019
Information Session

post_text:
Acadiana Renaissance Charter Academy Open Enrollment for the 2019-2020 school year is now open. If you would like to be entered into the lottery for a seat at our school, please fill out an application at acadianacharter.org.

We also have an Information Session Scheduled for this Thursday, January 17th, at 5:30pm. The meeting will take place in our school cafeteria. You will have the opportunity to learn about our school, ask questions, and get a tour of our campus.

Please call the school at 337-374-1209, ext. 1009, if you have any questions regarding enrollment.

post_text:
It is a proud day at ARCA when 24 of our teachers are nominated for the LEF Teacher of the Year! We are so proud of all our teachers! We are truly blessed with an amazing team! Thank you to the parents and students who took the time to nominate. Congrats to the following teachers:
Sarah Angel, Elizabeth Chiasson, Wendy Comeaux,
Sarah Couvillion, Sadie Cox, Elizabeth Daigle, Tim Davis, Kandice Dominic, Emily Dore, Cheryl Dugas, Daniel Fanguy, Jessica Heard, Robin Hochkeppel, Olivia Leger, Jamie Lejeune, Arlecia Malveaux, Kelly Martin, Brandi Menard, Jason Millet, Pamela Pry, Larissa Roque, Alisha Templet, Lori Vincent, and
Seth Zirlott

post_text:
MARK YOUR CALENDARS:

Open Enrollment for the 2019-2020 school year begins January 14th and ends February 15th, 2019. All applications submitted within the Open Enrollment period will have an equal opportunity for admission, regardless of whether they are submitted on the first day or the last day of Open Enrollment.

We will have an Information Session for Prospective Parents on January 17th at 5pm in our school cafeteria. We will have a presentation on our school, give parents the opportunity to ask questions and wrap up with a school tour.

post_text: Acadiana Renaissance will not have school on Thursday, November 1, 2018, due to the threat of severe weather when buses and parents would be bringing students to school. Stay safe everyone.

post_text: Did you know that you can still order spirit gear? Go to our school store website acadianacharterschool.com to place your orders.

post_text: Order Spirit Gear by August 24th!!!
shared_text:
Acadiana Renaissance Charter Academy - Official
August 2, 2018 at 7:46 AM ·

2018-2019 Spirit Gear is still available for purchase through our online store:www.acadianacharterschool.com.

To order, you must create an account or log in to your previously created account. You will receive a confirmation email once your purchase is complete.

$15 - short sleeve
$20 - long sleeve
$25 - sweatshirt
*NEW* $15 - Yard Sign

All spirit gear ordered by 5pm, August 24th, will be delivered the first week of September.

Orders can only be taken online. Please do not send payments to the school.

If you have any questions regarding Spirit Gear, please contact Bethanie Washington (bwashington@acadianacharter.org).

post_text: Please stop by and check out ARCA’s Little Free Library right outside of our front cafeteria door. Please stop by, take a book, and leave a book in exchange. We are very thankful to Rachel Norris and our Girl Scouts Troop for this wonderful addition! The Girl Scout Troop leaders will review books in the Little Free Library periodically, but parents will also need to monitor their child’s selections. Let the book sharing begin!
